<br>
I may no longer be a member of any of the guilds involved in the Federation.  However..<br>
<br>
- I still have many friends and allies in the Federation<br>
- I will still continue to apply to raids, and if I am turned away I will not take it personally, because I know there is a reason I've been turned away, and it's not necessary that I know what that reason is.<br>
- I will still continue to invite the members of the Federation to any activity that I lead. <br>
- I will still ask for help from the members of the Federation, and I will still respond to any call for aid that comes from any of the members of the Federation. <br>
- I will continue to defend the name and honor of those people and guilds whom I consider friend, ally, or even innocent bystander.<br>
<br>
-YOU will note that the noun &quot;I&quot; appears there quit a few times. The reason is because that these are the ideals I hold. And if YOU don't like them, that's fine, because they're not yours, and you don't have to deal with them. <br>
<br>
Now.. in defense of the german language, please cease to use the term &quot;uber&quot; as something hateful. It is defined in translation as the word &quot;super.&quot; The term you are looking for, if you refer to those who seek to hurt others to advance themselves, is probably &quot;evil&quot; or &quot;malicious.&quot;<br>
<br>
I see nothing wrong with a determination to eliminate a creature, whether the drive is experience, treasure, or pride. I see no problem if whatever reward it is you seek, you seek for yourselves and yourselves alone, or perhaps you wish to share it with others brave enough to volunteer. Whatever the case, if your intent is not specifically to hurt other people with your actions, so be it. My best wishes on whatever endeavors you wish to take on, and on however you choose to take them on.<br>
<br>
~Kaycerzan Deusabsconditus, Knight of Valor.<br>
